# factree.fm — Architecture Rules

## Project Context

A private, single-room YouTube listening app for two users. Real-time sync via SpacetimeDB.
Think Spotify Jam but for YouTube — one room, one queue, one vibe.

---

## State Architecture — Hard Rules

**SpacetimeDB is the single source of truth for all shared state.**

| What | Where | Access pattern |
|---|---|---|
| Currently playing video | `now_playing` table (singleton) | `useTable(tables.now_playing)` |
| Song queue | `queue_item` table | `useTable(tables.queue_item)` |
| Chat messages | `message` table | `useTable(tables.message)` |
| Online users | `user` table | `useTable(tables.user.where(r => r.online.eq(true)))` |
| Volume | `localStorage` | `localStorage.getItem/setItem` — user-local preference |
| Input drafts, edit mode, loading flags | React `useState` | ephemeral, per-client only |

**Rules:**
1. Never use React state or context for data shared between users — it belongs in a SpacetimeDB table
2. Never optimistically update local state — let the subscription update drive the render
3. Never read `conn.reducers` return values — reducers are transactional and return nothing

