## CSS Conventions

**Always use CSS custom properties. Never hardcode colors or font stacks.**

```css
/* ✅ */
color: var(--accent);
background: var(--surface);
font-family: 'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif; /* OK for display text */

/* ❌ */
color: #e8a030;
background: #1e160a;
```

### Design Token Reference (`src/index.css`)

| Token | Role |
|---|---|
| `--accent` | Warm amber — primary brand, CTA buttons, highlights |
| `--accent-dim` | Darkened amber — hover state for accent elements |
| `--accent-glow` | Translucent amber — focus ring on inputs |
| `--accent-contrast` | Dark text on amber backgrounds |
| `--bg` | Page background |
| `--text` | Primary text |
| `--text-muted` | Secondary / meta text |
| `--border` | Dividers, card borders |
| `--surface` | Card / panel background |
| `--surface-own` | Your own message / queue item highlight |
| `--surface-hover` | Hover state for interactive surfaces |
| `--textbox-color` | Input field background |

### Typography Stack

| Role | Font |
|---|---|
| Logo / song titles / headings | `'Playfair Display', Georgia, serif` |
| Body text / chat messages | `'Lora', Georgia, serif` |
| Labels / timestamps / monospace | `'IBM Plex Mono', 'Courier New', monospace` |

### Class Naming

- kebab-case, scoped to component: `.queue-item`, `.chat-message-sender`, `.player-controls`
- All styles live in `App.css`, organized by component with section comments
- Add new tokens to `index.css`, not inline

