## Framer Motion Conventions

```typescript
// Song/state transitions — wait for exit before enter
<AnimatePresence mode="wait">
  <motion.div key={nowPlaying?.queueItemId.toString()} ... />
</AnimatePresence>

// List items that appear/disappear dynamically
<AnimatePresence mode="popLayout">
  {items.map(item => <motion.div key={item.id.toString()} ... />)}
</AnimatePresence>

// Staggered list entrance
const container = { visible: { transition: { staggerChildren: 0.07 } } };
const item = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 8 },
  visible: { opacity: 1, y: 0, transition: { duration: 0.2, ease: 'easeOut' as const } },
};

// Keep transitions short — snappy over dramatic
transition={{ duration: 0.2 }}  // ✅ max ~0.3s for UI transitions
transition={{ duration: 0.8 }}  // ❌ too slow for interactive elements
```

**Note:** `ease: 'easeOut' as const` is required — Framer Motion's `Easing` type is a
literal union, not `string`. TypeScript will error without the `as const` assertion.

