## SpacetimeDB Integration

See `spacetimedb-typescript.mdc` for full SDK rules. Project-specific patterns:

```typescript
// Reading data — always destructure as tuple
const [rows, isLoading] = useTable(tables.tableName);

// Filtered subscription (indexed column)
const [onlineUsers] = useTable(tables.user.where(r => r.online.eq(true)));

// Mutations — object syntax, not positional
const addToQueue = useReducer(reducers.addToQueue);
addToQueue({ videoId, title, thumbnailUrl });  // ✅
addToQueue(videoId, title, thumbnailUrl);      // ❌

// Identity comparison
row.addedBy.isEqual(identity)          // ✅
row.addedBy === identity               // ❌ — reference equality doesn't work

// Timestamps
new Date(Number(row.createdAt.microsSinceUnixEpoch / 1000n))  // ✅
new Date(row.createdAt)                                        // ❌
```

### Backend Layout

```
spacetimedb/src/
├── schema.ts   Tables definition + `export default spacetimedb`
└── index.ts    Reducers + clientConnected/clientDisconnected hooks
```

After any backend change:
1. `npm run spacetime:publish` — deploy to maincloud
2. `npm run spacetime:generate` — regenerate `src/module_bindings/`
3. Commit the updated bindings

---

## TypeScript Rules

- `strict: true` is enforced — no exceptions
- No `any` — use `unknown` + type guards or proper generics
- `import type` for type-only imports — enforced by ESLint
- BigInt literals for `u64`/`i64` fields: `0n`, `1n`, not `0`, `1`

---

## YouTube IFrame API

The `<div ref={wrapperRef}>` in `PlayerPanel` is **intentionally outside React's virtual DOM**.
YouTube replaces it with an `<iframe>`, which React cannot manage. Never:
- Conditionally render `wrapperRef`
- Move the YouTube player DOM node
- Recreate the `YT.Player` instance on re-render

All playback sync logic lives in `src/hooks/useYouTubeSync.ts`.
